  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 604b577af8a43c942bd5251f25245dcd, type: 3}
  m_Name: Vimana_Lore
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::GV.UI.ShipLoreData
  shipName: Vimana
  tagline: Forged before memory. Powered by faith. Older than every kingdom it serves.
  rarity: Epic
  shipClass: Ancient Divine Carrier
  originLabel: Realm
  originName: Akasa Raajyas
  factionLabel: Pilots
  factionName: Sarathi
  powerSystem: Astra-Powered Thara Core
  combatRole: Multi-role divine platform
  specialAbility: "Thara Surge - channels accumulated spiritual energy into a devastating
    area pulse that disrupts enemy targeting systems and temporarily supercharges
    all Astra weapons."
  backstory: "No one built the Vimanas. They were found. Deep beneath the floating
    peaks of Garuda Vana, inside sealed chambers that predate every kingdom in the
    Akasa Raajyas, the first Vimanas were discovered during the Age of Excavation.
    The Devas of Nandana claimed divine right over them. The Yakshas of Ratna Shila
    insisted they were sacred treasures to be guarded, not flown. The Garudajas simply
    took them and learned to fly. The truth is that nobody knows who created the Vimanas
    or why. Their hulls are forged from an alloy that no modern smith can replicate
    - lighter than bamboo, harder than volcanic diamond. Their power cores run on
    Thara - the spiritual resonance energy that flows through the Akasa Raajyas like
    an invisible river. Every kingdom eventually claimed Vimanas of their own. Nandana's
    royal fleet. Ratna Shila's guardian escorts. Daitya Giri's forge-modified war
    variants. Garuda Vana's wind-runners. The Sarathi are the pilots chosen by the
    Vimanas themselves - each vessel bonds with its pilot through Thara Resonance,
    and a bonded Vimana will not fly for anyone else. The bond is permanent. If the
    pilot dies, the Vimana goes silent until a new resonance is found, which can take
    generations."
  strengths: "Divine-alloy hull absorbs punishment that would shred any manufactured
    vessel\nThara Core provides near-limitless energy to pilots with strong resonance\nAstra
    weapon integration - Vimanas amplify the pilot's Astra class by channeling Thara
    through ancient weapon mounts\nSelf-repairing hull slowly regenerates damage between
    engagements using ambient Thara energy"
  weaknesses: "Irreplaceable - if a Vimana is destroyed, it is gone forever; no one
    can build new ones\nThara dependency means performance drops sharply in low-resonance
    zones far from the Akasa Raajyas\nAncient systems are unpredictable; critical
    functions sometimes activate or deactivate without warning\nThe pilot bond means
    no backup pilots - if the Sarathi is incapacitated, the Vimana is grounded"
  history: "Discovered beneath Garuda Vana's floating peaks during the Age of Excavation\nNandana's
    Devas claim divine ownership; the Vimana Wars begin between kingdoms\nYakshas
    of Ratna Shila seal dozens of Vimanas in protected vaults, refusing to weaponize
    them\nGarudajas become the first true Vimana pilots, learning flight through instinct
    and wind\nDaitya Giri's Asura forges modify recovered Vimanas with volcanic-ore
    weapon mounts\nThe Sarathi tradition is formalized - pilots chosen by Thara bond,
    not by birth or rank\nAtom Riders appear with Nuclear-P Spaceships, challenging
    Vimana air supremacy for the first time"
